abstract: The House Judiciary Committee abruptly postponed a historic vote on articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump, shutting down a 14-hour session that dragged with partisanship but had been expected to end with the formal charges being sent to the full House for a vote next week. Approval of the two charges  against the president is still expected Friday in the committee.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House Judiciary Committee abruptly postponed a historic vote on articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump, shutting down a 14-hour session that dragged with partisanship but had been expected to end with the formal charges being sent to the full House for a vote next week. Approval of the two charges against the president is still expected Friday in the committee.
headline_main: House Committee Delays Historic Vote on Trump Impeachment
headline_print_headline: House Committee Delays Historic Vote on Trump Impeachment

abstract: How Putin kept a meeting of the leaders of France, Germany, Russia and Ukraine from moving closer to an end of a calamitous five-year war.
snippet: How Putin kept a meeting of the leaders of France, Germany, Russia and Ukraine from moving closer to an end of a calamitous five-year war.
lead_paragraph: The France-Germany-Russia-Ukraine summit meeting in Paris on Monday, seeking ways to end the war ravaging eastern Ukraine, ended with a few promising words but no progress in reality. Russia, the aggressor, continues to keep the Ukrainian territory it seized in 2014, and Ukraine’s new president, Volodymyr Zelensky, showed he can’t easily be pressured into surrender.

abstract: The panel will meet to debate the charges against President Trump before voting to send them to the full House.
snippet: The panel will meet to debate the charges against President Trump before voting to send them to the full House.
lead_paragraph: The House Judiciary Committee will convene Thursday morning to debate two articles of impeachment against President Trump, the final step before Democrats bring them to the House floor for an expected vote next week to charge the president with high crimes and misdemeanors.

headline_print_headline: Eyeing 2020, House Empowers Medicare to Negotiate Drug Costs

abstract: The dollar jumped against the safe-haven Japanese yen on Thursday after U.S. President Donald Trump said the United States was "very close" to nailing down a trade deal with China,  just days before new U.S. tariffs on Chinese imports were due to be imposed.
snippet: The dollar jumped against the safe-haven Japanese yen on Thursday after U.S. President Donald Trump said the United States was "very close" to nailing down a trade deal with China,  just days before new U.S. tariffs on Chinese imports were due to ...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — The dollar jumped against the safe-haven Japanese yen on Thursday after U.S. President Donald Trump said the United States was "very close" to nailing down a trade deal with China, just days before new U.S. tariffs on Chinese imports were due to be imposed.
headline_main: Dollar Jumps Versus Yen as Risk Appetite Returns on U.S.-China Trade Deal Hopes
headline_print_headline: Dollar Jumps Versus Yen as Risk Appetite Returns on U.S.-China Trade Deal Hopes

abstract: Abdullah Abdullah, a three-time contender for the presidency, is again at the center of an electoral crisis. This time, he insists he won’t compromise.
snippet: Abdullah Abdullah, a three-time contender for the presidency, is again at the center of an electoral crisis. This time, he insists he won’t compromise.
lead_paragraph: KABUL, Afghanistan — Three months after Afghanistan’s presidential vote, the entire electoral process is stalled in a dispute that Afghan and Western officials say could pose an even greater threat to stability than the last such crisis, five years ago.

abstract: A U.S. Senate committee backed legislation on Wednesday to impose sanctions on Turkey after its offensive in Syria and purchase of a Russian S-400 missile system, the latest move in the chamber to push Republican President Donald Trump to take a harder line against Ankara.
snippet: A U.S. Senate committee backed legislation on Wednesday to impose sanctions on Turkey after its offensive in Syria and purchase of a Russian S-400 missile system, the latest move in the chamber to push Republican President Donald Trump to take a h...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A U.S. Senate committee backed legislation on Wednesday to impose sanctions on Turkey after its offensive in Syria and purchase of a Russian S-400 missile system, the latest move in the chamber to push Republican President Donald Trump to take a harder line against Ankara.
headline_main: U.S. Senate Committee Approves Turkey Sanctions Bill
headline_print_headline: U.S. Senate Committee Approves Turkey Sanctions Bill

abstract: The hour lent a prime-time urgency to the spectacle, but both sides reverted to boilerplate.
snippet: The hour lent a prime-time urgency to the spectacle, but both sides reverted to boilerplate.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — They might as well have been speaking different languages, from alternate realities. They spoke mostly past each other, late into the cable night and into history.
